#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kgpg; is a simple interface for GnuPG, a powerful encryption utility. GnuPG "
"(also known as gpg) is included in most distributions and should be "
"installed on your system. You can get the latest version on <ulink url="
"\"https://gnupg.org\">https://gnupg.org</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"&kgpg; je enostaven vmesnik za GnuPG, ki je zmogljiv pripomoček za "
"šifriranje. GnuPG (znan tudi kot gpg) je vključen v večini distribucijah in "
"bi že moral biti nameščen na vašem sistemu. Najnovejšo različico dobite na "
"<ulink url=\"https://gnupg.org\">https://gnupg.org</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With &kgpg; you will be able to encrypt and decrypt your files and emails, "
"allowing much more secure communications. A mini howto on encryption with "
"gpg is available on <ulink url=\"https://www.gnupg.org/documentation/howtos."
"en.html\">GnuPG's web site</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Z &kgpg; boste lahko šifrirali in dešifrirali vaše datoteke in elektronska "
"sporočila in s tem zagotovili precej bolj varno komunikacijo. Kratka "
"navodila za uporabo gpg-ja so dostopna na <ulink url=\"https://www.gnupg.org/"
"documentation/howtos.en.html\">Spletni strani GnuPG</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With &kgpg;, you don't need to remember gpg's command lines and options. "
"Almost everything can be done with a few mouse clicks."
msgstr ""
"Pri &kgpg; vam ne bo potrebno zapomniti se gpg-jevih ukaznih vrstic in "
"njegovih možnosti. Skoraj vse lahko storite z nekaj kliki na miško."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr "Začetek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a list of &kgpg;'s main components:"
msgstr "Tu je seznam glavnih komponent &kgpg;-ja:"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "System Tray Icon"
msgstr "Ikona v Sistemski Vrstici"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kgpg; system tray applet"
msgstr "aplet sistemske vrstice &kgpg;-ja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you start &kgpg;, a system tray icon will appear. A &LMB; click will "
"open the Key Manager window, while a &RMB; click will open a menu allowing "
"quick access to some important features. If you prefer other options you can "
"change the &LMB; action to show the editor or completely disable the system "
"tray icon using the <link linkend=\"conf-misc\">settings dialog</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ko zaženete &kgpg;, se bo v sistemski vrstici prikazala ikona. Z levim "
"klikom odprete okno Upravljalnika s Ključi, z desnim klikom pa odprete meni, "
"ki omogoča hitri dostop do nekaj pomembnih funkcij. Če bi raje videli, da "
"ima vaš levi klik drugačno dejanje, npr. da prikaže urejevalnik ali "
"onemogoči sistemski pladenj, lahko to spremenite z <link linkend=\"conf-misc"
"\">nastavitvenim pogovornim oknom</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please note that the system tray icon of &kgpg; is marked as &quot;"
"inactive&quot; basically all the time. Since the system tray applet will "
"usually hide inactive icons the one of &kgpg; will not be shown until you "
"explicitly request it. For details please have a look at the &plasma; "
"documentation."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da je ikona &kgpg;-ja v sistemski vrstici označena kot &quot;"
"nedejavna&quot; cel čas. Ker programček sistemske vrstice ponavadi skrije "
"nedejavne ikone, bo tudi ikona &kgpg;-ja skrita dokler je ne boste izrecno "
"zahtevali. Za več podrobnosti si poglejte dokumentacijo za &plasma;."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key Manager Window"
msgstr "Okno Upravljalnika s Ključi"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key manager window"
msgstr "Okno upravljalnika s ključi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"That's the central place to manage your keys. To open the <link linkend="
"\"keymanager\">Key Manager window</link>, click with the &LMB; on &kgpg;'s "
"applet. You can import, export, sign and edit your keys. Most actions can be "
"performed with a &RMB; click on a key."
msgstr ""
"To je mesto, kjer upravljate s svojimi ključi. Da odprete <link linkend="
"\"keymanager\">okno Upravljalnika s Ključi</link>, kliknite z levim klikom "
"na &kgpg;-jevo ikono v sistemski vrstici. Svoje ključe lahko uvozite, "
"izvozite in urejate. Večino dejanj se izvede z desnim klikom na ključ."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editor Window"
msgstr "Okno Urejevalnika"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editor window"
msgstr "Okno urejevalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It's a simple text editor, where you can type or paste text to encrypt/"
"decrypt it. To open the <link linkend=\"editor\">editor</link>, click with "
"the &RMB; on &kgpg;'s applet."
msgstr ""
"To je enostaven urejevalnik besedila, kjer lahko vtipkate ali prilepite "
"besedilo, ki ga želite šifrirati/dešifrirati. Da odprete <link linkend="
"\"editor\">urejevalnik</link>, lahko kliknete z desnim klikom na &kgpg;-jevo "
"ikono v sistemski vrstici."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "File manager integration"
msgstr "Integracija upravljalnika z datotekami"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kgpg; is integrated in &konqueror; and &dolphin;. It means that when you "
"right click on a file, you can choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Actions</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Encrypt File</guimenuitem></menuchoice> to encrypt a "
"file. You can decrypt a file with a &LMB; click."
msgstr ""
"&kgpg; je integriran v &konqueror; in &dolphin;. To pomeni, da ko kliknete z "
"desnim klikom na datoteko, lahko iz menija izberete "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Dejavnosti</guimenu><guimenuitem>Šifriraj Datoteko</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Datoteko lahko dešifrirate z &LMB; klikom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &kgpg;"
msgstr "Uporaba &kgpg;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are two ways to encrypt your data:"
msgstr "Obstajata dva načina da šifrirate svoje podatke:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Symmetrical encryption: your data is just encrypted with a password. Anybody "
"who has a computer with gpg can decrypt your message if you give him/her the "
"password. To perform a symmetrical encryption, choose \"symmetrical "
"encryption\" in the options box when asked to choose an encryption key."
msgstr ""
"Simetrično kriptiranje: vaši podatki so zašifrirani le z geslom. Vsakdo, ki "
"ima računalnik z gpg-jem lahko dešifrira vaše sporočilo, če dobi vaše geslo. "
"Da izvedete simetrično kriptiranje, izberite \"simetrično šifriranje\" med "
"možnostmi, ko ste povprašani po izbiri enkripcijskega ključa."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Key encryption: you must first create your key pair (secret key and public "
"key) and give a passphrase. Keep your secret key in a safe place, and "
"exchange your public key with your friends. Then, if you want to send an "
"encrypted message to Alex, you must encrypt the message with Alex's public "
"key. To decrypt the message, the recipient will need Alex's secret key and "
"passphrase."
msgstr ""
"Kriptiranje s ključi: najprej morate ustvariti svoj par ključev (zasebni in "
"javni ključ) in podati šifrirno frazo. Svoj zasebni ključ skrbno shranite, "
"javni ključ pa izmenjajte s svojimi prijatelji. Če želite poslati sporočilo "
"npr. Alešu, morate šifrirati svoje sporočilo z Aleševim javnim ključem. Tako "
"bo moral prejemnik uporabiti Alešev zasebni ključ in Šifrirno frazo, da "
"dešifrira vaše sporočilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Key encryption is a bit more complicated (you must exchange keys with your "
"friends) but safer. Remember that if you encrypt a message with someone "
"else's key, you will not be able to decrypt it. You can only decrypt "
"messages that have been encrypted with your public key."
msgstr ""
"Kriptiranje s ključi je nekoliko zahtevnejše (svoje javne ključe morate "
"izmenjati s svojimi prijatelji), vendar je varneje. Če šifrirate sporočilo z "
"javnim ključem nekoga drugega, ga vi sami ne boste mogli dešifrirati. Vi "
"lahko dešifrirate le tista sporočila, ki so bila šifrirana z vašim javnim "
"ključem."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generating a key"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje ključa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:174
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you don't have a key, &kgpg; will automatically pop up the key generation "
"dialog at the first startup. You can also access it in the Key Manager from "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Keys</guimenu><guimenuitem>Generate Key Pair</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Če še nimate ključa, se vam bo ob prvem zagonu samodejno pojavilo pogovorno "
"okno &kgpg;-ja za ustvarjanje ključa. Do tega pogovornega okna lahko "
"dostopate tudi sami iz menija Upravljalnika Ključev pod "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Ključi</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ustvari par ključev</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key generation dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno za ustvarjanje ključa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Simply enter your name, Email address and click <guibutton>Ok</guibutton>. "
"This will generate a standard gpg key. If you want more options, you can "
"click on the <guibutton>Expert Mode</guibutton> button, which will bring up "
"a &konsole; window with all of gpg's options."
msgstr ""
"Vnesite svoje ime, E-poštni naslov in kliknite <guibutton>V redu</"
"guibutton>. S tem boste ustvarili standardni gpg ključ. Če želite več "
"možnosti, lahko kliknete na gumb <guibutton>Napredni Način</guibutton>, ki "
"odpre okno &konsole; z vsemi gpg možnostmi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many people play around with their first key, generate bad user ids, add "
"comments they later regret or simply forget their passphrase. To avoid such "
"keys to stay valid forever it's usually a good idea to limit the lifetime to "
"some 12 month. You can modify the lifetime of your secret keys later using "
"the <link linkend=\"keyproperties\">key properties window</link>."
msgstr ""
"Mnogi ljudje se poigravajo s svojim prvim ključem, ustvarjajo napačne "
"uporabniške ID-je, dodajajo komentarje, ki jih pozneje obžalujejo, ali "
"preprosto pozabijo svojo šifrirno frazo. Da bi preprečili, da bi takšni "
"ključi ostali veljavni za vedno, je običajno dobro, da omejite življenjsko "
"dobo na približno 12 mesecev. Pozneje lahko spremenite življenjsko dobo "
"svojih skrivnih ključev z uporabo <link linkend=\"keyproperties\">okna "
"Lastnosti ključa</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid "Revoking a key"
msgstr "Preklic ključa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A key pair that has expired can be brought back into an operational state as "
"long as you have access to the private key and the passphrase. To reliably "
"render a key unusable you need to revoke it. Revoking is done by adding a "
"special revocation signature to the key."
msgstr ""
"Pretečeni ključ se da ponovno obnoviti in uporabljati, dokler imate dostop "
"do zasebnega ključa in šifrirne fraze. Če želite zanesljivo narediti ključ "
"neuporaben, ga morate preklicati. Preklic se izvede tako, da se ključu doda "
"poseben preklicni podpis."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:208
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This revocation signature can be created together with the key. In this case "
"it is stored in a separate file. This file can later be imported into the "
"keyring and is then attached to the key rendering it unusable. Please note "
"that to import this signature to the key no password is required. Therefore "
"you should store this revocation signature in a safe place, usually one that "
"is different from you key pair. It is a good advise to use a place that is "
"detached from your computer, either copy it to an external storage device "
"like an USB stick or print it out."
msgstr ""
"Ta podpis preklica lahko ustvarite skupaj s ključem. V tem primeru je "
"shranjen v ločeni datoteki. To datoteko je mogoče pozneje uvoziti v shrambo "
"za ključe in jo nato priložiti ključu, zaradi česar postane neuporaben. "
"Upoštevajte, da za uvoz tega podpisa v ključ ni potrebno geslo. Zato morate "
"ta podpis preklica shraniti na varno mesto, običajno na mesto, ki se "
"razlikuje od vašega para ključev. Priporočljivo je, da uporabite mesto, ki "
"je ločeno od računalnika, na primer kopirajte ga na zunanjo napravo za "
"shranjevanje, kot je ključek USB, ali ga natisnite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have not created such a detached revocation on key creation you can "
"create such a revocation signature at any time choosing "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Keys</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Revoke key</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>, optionally importing it to your keyring immediately."
msgstr ""
"Če niste ustvarili takšnega ločenega preklica med ustvarjanjem ključa, lahko "
"to storite kadarkoli tako, da v meniju izberete <menuchoice><guimenu>Ključi</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Prekliči ključ</guimenuitem></menuchoice> in ga "
"neobvezno takoj uvozite v svojo zbirko ključev."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encrypting Your Data"
msgstr "Šifriranje Vaših Podatkov"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encrypting a file from &konqueror; or Dolphin"
msgstr "Šifriranje datoteke preko &konqueror;-ja ali Dolphin-a"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:231
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click on the file you want to encrypt with the &RMB;. Choose "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Actions</guimenu><guimenuitem>Encrypt File</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> in the pop up menu. You will then be prompted with "
"the Public key selection dialog. Choose the key of the recipient and click "
"<guibutton>Encrypt</guibutton>. The encrypted file will be saved with a "
"<literal role=\"extension\">.asc</literal> or <literal role=\"extension\">."
"gpg</literal> extension depending on whether you chose <guilabel>ASCII "
"armored encryption</guilabel> or not. ASCII encrypted files only use "
"readable characters to represent the data resulting in files that are more "
"robust when copied around or sent by mail but are one third larger."
msgstr ""
"Z desnim klikom kliknite na datoteko, ki jo želite enkriptirati. Izberite "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Dejavnosti</guimenu><guimenuitem>Šifiriraj Datoteko</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> v prikazanem meniju. Nato boste pozvani s "
"pogovornim oknom za izbiro javnega ključa. Izberite ključ prejemnika in "
"kliknite <guibutton>V redu</guibutton>. Šifrirana datoteka bo shranjena s "
"končnico <literal role=\"extension\">.asc</literal> ali <literal role="
"\"extension\">.gpg</literal>, odvisno, ali ste izbrali <guilabel>Šifriranje "
"na podlagi ASCII</guilabel> ali ne. Datoteke, šifrirane na podlagi ASCII, "
"uporabljajo le berljive znake za predstavitev podatkov, kar napravi datoteke "
"bolj robustne in odporne na spremembe, ko se jih kopira naokoli ali pošilja "
"prek e-pošte, vendar so za tretjino večje."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:235
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a screen shot of the key selection window"
msgstr "Tu je posnetek zaslona okna za izbiro ključa"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encrypting a text with &kgpg;'s applet"
msgstr "Šifriranje besedila z &kgpg;-jevim apletom v sistemski vrstici"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can encrypt the contents of the clipboard by selecting the "
"<guimenuitem>Encrypt clipboard</guimenuitem> item in applet menu. When you "
"choose <guimenuitem>Sign clipboard</guimenuitem> then the text will be "
"signed instead. Both actions will import the current clipboard contents into "
"an <link linkend=\"editor\">editor window</link>, perform the requested "
"action and paste the contents back into the editor."
msgstr ""
"Vsebino odložišča lahko zašifrirate tako, da izberete <guimenuitem>Šifriraj "
"odložišče</guimenuitem> v meniju apleta v sistemski vrstici. Če namesto "
"izberete <guimenuitem>Podpiši odložišče</guimenuitem>, bo besedilo "
"podpisano. Obe dejanji uvozita trenutno vsebino odložišča v <link linkend="
"\"editor\">okno urejevalnika</link>, nato se izvede zahtevano dejanje, "
"vsebina pa se prilepi nazaj v urejevalnik."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encrypting text from &kgpg;'s editor"
msgstr "Šifriranje besedila iz &kgpg;-jevega urejevalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is as simple as clicking on the <guibutton>Encrypt</guibutton> button. "
"You will then be prompted with the Public key selection dialog. Choose your "
"key and click <guibutton>Ok</guibutton>. The encrypted message will appear "
"in the editor window."
msgstr ""
"To se naredi preprosto s klikom na gumb <guibutton>Šifriraj</guibutton>. "
"Nato boste pozvani z pogovornim oknom za Izbiro javnega ključa. Izberite "
"ključ in kliknite <guibutton>V redu</guibutton>. Šifrirano besedilo se bo "
"prikazalo v oknu urejevalnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Usually you can only encrypt files with keys that are trusted by you. Since "
"you sometimes want to just send a confident note to some random people you "
"are aware of having a GPG key you can set the option <guilabel>Allow "
"encryption with untrusted keys</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Običajno lahko datoteke šifrirate samo s ključi, ki jim zaupate. Ker želite "
"včasih poslati samozavestno sporočilo nekaterim naključnim osebam, za katere "
"veste, da imajo ključ GPG, lahko nastavite možnost <guilabel>Dovoli "
"šifriranje s ključi, ki niso zaupanja vredni</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:270
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To make sure that you can decrypt every file you have encrypted even if they "
"are encrypted with someone else's key you can use the options "
"<guilabel>Always encrypt with</guilabel> and <guilabel>Encrypt files with</"
"guilabel> which are available in the <link linkend=\"conf-encryption\">KGpg "
"configuration</link>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite zagotoviti, da lahko dešifrirate vsako datoteko, ki ste jo "
"šifrirali, tudi če je šifrirana s ključem nekoga drugega, lahko uporabite "
"možnosti <guilabel>Vedno šifriraj z</guilabel> in <guilabel>Šifriraj "
"datoteke z</guilabel>, ki sta dostopni v <link linkend=\"conf-encryption"
"\">Nastavi KGpg</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information on the encryption options <guilabel>ASCII armor</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Allow encryption with untrusted keys</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Symmetrical encryption</guilabel>, please refer to gpg's "
"documentation or <ulink url=\"man:gpg\">man pages</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Za več informacij o enkripcijskih možnostih <guilabel>ASCII oklep</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Dovoli šifriranje s ključi, ki niso zaupanja vredni</"
"guilabel> in <guilabel>Simetrično šifriranje</guilabel>, se obrnite na gpg-"
"jevo dokumentacijo ali <ulink url=\"man:gpg\">strani priročnika</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:284
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decrypting Your Data"
msgstr "Dešifriranje Vaših podatkov"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decrypting a file from &konqueror; or &dolphin;"
msgstr "Dešifriranje datoteke iz &konqueror;-ja ali &dolphin;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<mousebutton>Left</mousebutton> click on the file you want to decrypt. Enter "
"your passphrase and it will be decrypted. You can also drag an encrypted "
"text file and drop it into &kgpg;'s editor window. It will then ask the "
"passphrase and open the decrypted text in &kgpg;'s editor. You can even drop "
"remote files ! You can also use the <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Decrypt File</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and choose a "
"file to decrypt."
msgstr ""
"Kliknite z <mousebutton>levim</mousebutton> klikom na datoteko, ki jo želite "
"dešifrirati. Vnesite šifrirno frazo in datoteka bo dešifrirana. Prav tako "
"lahko povlečete dešifrirane besedilne datoteke in jih spustite v &kgpg;-jev "
"urejevalnik. Ta vas bo nato povprašal po šifrirni frazi in nato odprl "
"dešifrirano besedilo. To lahko naredite celo z oddaljenimi datotekami! "
"Uporabite lahko tudi <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Odšifriraj datoteko</guimenuitem></menuchoice> in "
"izberete datoteko, ki jo želite dešifrirati."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:300
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decrypting text with &kgpg;'s applet"
msgstr "Dešifriranje besedila z &kgpg;-jevim apletom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also decrypt the contents of the clipboard with the "
"<guimenuitem>Decrypt Clipboard</guimenuitem> menu entry of the &kgpg; "
"applet. An <link linkend=\"editor\">editor window</link> will show up with "
"the decrypted text."
msgstr ""
"Dešifrirate lahko tudi vsebino odložišča tako, da izberete "
"<guimenuitem>Odšifriraj Odložišče</guimenuitem> v meniju &kgpg;-jevega "
"apleta v sistemski vrstici. Prikazalo se bo <link linkend=\"editor\">okno "
"urejevalnika</link> z dešifriranim besedilom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decrypting a text from the editor"
msgstr "Dešifriranje besedila iz urejevalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy or Drag and Drop the text you want to decrypt, and click on the "
"<guibutton>Decrypt</guibutton> button. You will be prompted for the "
"passphrase."
msgstr ""
"Kopirajte ali povlecite besedilo v urejevalnik in kliknite na gumb "
"<guibutton>Odšifriraj</guibutton>. Ponovno boste povprašani po šifrirni "
"frazi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key Management"
msgstr "Upravljanje s ključi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All basic key management options can be performed through &kgpg;. To open "
"the key management window click the &LMB; on &kgpg;'s applet. Most options "
"are available with a <mousebutton>right</mousebutton> click on a key. To "
"import/export public keys, you can use drag and drop or the Copy/Paste "
"keyboard shortcuts."
msgstr ""
"Vse osnovne možnosti upravljanja se da izvesti preko &kgpg;-ja. Da odprete "
"okno za upravljanje s ključi, kliknite z levim klikom na &kgpg;-jev aplet. "
"Večina možnosti je dostopnih z <mousebutton>desnim</mousebutton> klikom na "
"ključ. Da uvozite/izvozite javne ključe, lahko to storite da jih povlečete z "
"miško ali uporabite bljižnice za kopiranje/prilepljenje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can export a public key via email, to the clipboard, to a keyserver or "
"to a local file. Use the options in the export dialog to export everything, "
"export without attributes (photo ids) or export a clean key &ie; the key "
"itself including its subkeys, but excluding all signatures."
msgstr ""
"Javni ključ lahko izvozite v odložišče, v strežnik s ključi, v lokalno "
"datoteko ali po e-pošti. Uporabite možnosti v pogovornem oknu za izvoz, da "
"izvozite celoten ključ, izvozite brez atributov (fotografskih ID_jev) ali pa "
"izvozite čisti ključ &ie; sam ključ, vključno s podključi, vendar brez "
"kakršnih koli podpisov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:335
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key Manager"
msgstr "Upravljalnik Ključev"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here's a screen shot of key management"
msgstr "Tu je posnetek zaslona upravljalnika ključev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this example you see a key group containing two keys, two key pairs and "
"three public keys. The third column shows the trust you have in the keys. "
"The first key pair is ultimately trusted and is also set as the default key "
"(bold font) while the second one has expired. Two of the public keys are "
"fully trusted while the trust of the last key is marginal. The last key is "
"expanded, showing it's ElGamal subkey, an additional user id, both also with "
"marginal trust, and some of it's signatures."
msgstr ""
"V tem primeru vidite skupino ključev, ki vsebuje dva ključa, dva para "
"ključev in tri javne ključe. Tretji stolpec prikazuje vaše zaupanje v "
"ključe. Prvi par ključev je popolno zaupanja vreden in je tudi nastavljen "
"kot privzeti ključ (krepka pisava), drugi pa je potekel. Dvema javnima "
"ključema se polno zaupa, medtem ko je zaupanje zadnjega ključa delno. Zadnji "
"ključ je razširjen in prikazuje svoj podključ ElGamal, dodatni ID "
"uporabnika, oba tudi z delnim zaupanjem, in nekaj njegovih podpisov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Signatures allow navigating through your keyring. Double clicking on a "
"signature or a key shown as member of a group will jump directly to the "
"corresponding primary key."
msgstr ""
"Podpisi omogočajo navigacijo po vaši shrambi ključev. Dvojni klik na podpis "
"ali ključ, prikazan kot član skupine, bo skočil neposredno na ustrezni "
"primarni ključ."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:350
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key properties"
msgstr "Lastnosti ključa"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:353 index.docbook:391
#, no-c-format
msgid "The key properties window"
msgstr "Okno z lastnostmi ključa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While the key manager allows you to do general actions with one or multiple "
"keys, key groups or signatures, the key properties window gives you access "
"to a single key. You can reach it by pressing enter in the key manager or "
"double clicking the key."
msgstr ""
"Medtem ko vam upravitelj ključev omogoča izvajanje splošnih dejanj z enim "
"ali več ključi, skupinami ključev ali podpisi, vam okno z lastnostmi ključev "
"omogoča dostop do enega ključa. Do njega pridete tako, da v upravitelju "
"ključev pritisnete enter ali dvakrat kliknete na ključ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this window you can change the key passphrase and expiration of your "
"secret keys. For all keys you can also set the owner trust value."
msgstr ""
"V tem oknu lahko spremenite šifrirno frazo ključa in datum poteka vašega "
"skrivnega ključa. Za vse ključe lahko nastavite tudi stopnjo zaupanja "
"lastniku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This value indicates how much you trust the owner of this key to correctly "
"verify the identity of the keys he signs. Taking the owner trust into "
"account gpg creates your own web of trust. You trust the keys you signed. If "
"you assign owner trust to these persons you will also trust the keys they "
"have signed without the need that you first have to sign their keys too."
msgstr ""
"Ta vrednost označuje, koliko zaupate lastniku tega ključa, da bo pravilno "
"preveril identiteto ključev, ki jih podpiše. Upoštevanje zaupanja lastnika "
"gpg ustvari vašo lastno mrežo zaupanja. Zaupate ključem, ki ste jih "
"podpisali. Če tem osebam dodelite zaupanje, boste zaupali tudi ključem, ki "
"so jih podpisali, ne da bi morali najprej podpisati tudi njihove ključe."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:366
#, no-c-format
msgid "Signing keys"
msgstr "Podpisovanje ključev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you sign a key of someone else (let's call her Alice) you announce that "
"you are sure that this key really belongs to that person and the key can be "
"trusted. Of course you really should have checked that. This usually means "
"that you have to meet Alice, check at least one identity card and get the "
"full key fingerprint or a copy of her key. Then you go home and sign that "
"key. Usually you will later upload the newly signed key to a <link linkend="
"\"keyserver\">key server</link> so everyone knows you have checked that key "
"and the owner may be trusted. Alice will likely do the same so you both will "
"have your keys signed by the other one. If one of you has no identity card "
"at hand it's no problem if the signing happens in only direction."
msgstr ""
"Ko podpišete ključ nekoga drugega (recimo ji Ana), sporočate, da ste "
"prepričani, da ta ključ res pripada tej osebi in da ključu lahko zaupate. "
"Seveda bi to res morali preveriti. To običajno pomeni, da se morate srečati "
"z Ana, preveriti vsaj eno osebno izkaznico in dobiti celoten prstni odtis "
"ključa ali kopijo njenega ključa. Potem greste domov in podpišete tisti "
"ključ. Običajno boste pozneje naložili novo podpisani ključ na <link linkend="
"\"keyserver\">strežnik s ključi</link>, tako da vsi vedo, da ste preverili "
"ta ključ in lastniku lahko zaupate. Ana bo verjetno storila enako, tako da "
"bosta ključe podpisala oba. Če eden od vaju nima pri roki osebne izkaznice, "
"ni problema, če se podpis zgodi samo v eni smeri."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"But think about what happens if Alice lives on the other end of the world. "
"You communicate with her regularly but there is no chance you will see her "
"anytime soon. How do you trust her key?"
msgstr ""
"Zdaj pa pomislite, kaj se zgodi, če Ana živi na drugem koncu sveta. Z njo "
"lahko redno komunicirate, vendar ni možnosti, da bi se z njo lahko v kratkem "
"dobili v živo. Kako lahko zaupate njenemu ključu?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you select her key and then choose <guimenuitem>Sign Key...</"
"guimenuitem> you will get the dialog that allows you to choose the options "
"how you would like to sign that key."
msgstr ""
"Ko izberete njen ključ in nato <guimenuitem>Podpiši Ključ...</guimenuitem>, "
"se vam bo odprlo pogovorno okno, ki vam omogoča, da izberete možnosti, kako "
"želite podpisati ta ključ."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:375
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selecting a Secret Key for Signing"
msgstr "Izbira Skrivnega Ključa za Podpis"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First you can choose the key you will use to sign the key. Then you can "
"enter how carefully you checked that she really is the person she pretends "
"to be. This information will be stored together with the signature so it is "
"a guidance for everyone else who might need that signature (more on this "
"below). And then comes the option that would help you if you can't meet "
"Alice in person: <guilabel>Local signature (cannot be exported)</guilabel>. "
"When you activate that option a special version of a signature will be "
"created that can never even by accident leave you keyring."
msgstr ""
"Najprej lahko izberete ključ, s katerim boste podpisali ključ. Nato lahko "
"vnesete, kako natančno ste preverili, ali je res oseba, za katero se "
"predstavlja. Te informacije bodo shranjene skupaj s podpisom, tako da so "
"vodilo za vse ostale, ki morda potrebujejo ta podpis (več o tem spodaj). In "
"potem pride možnost, ki bi vam pomagala, če Ane ne morete osebno srečati: "
"<guilabel>Lokalni podpis (ni mogoče izvoziti)</guilabel>. Ko aktivirate to "
"možnost, se ustvari posebna različica podpisa, ki nikoli niti slučajno ne "
"more zapustiti vaše shrambe s ključi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"But why is it important how carefully you checked Alice's identity? Who "
"should care? There is a different way to solve your problem with the "
"identity of Alice. If you can't visit Alice anytime soon just think of "
"Trent. You know Trent has a keypair, too. And Trent is a globetrotter, being "
"on a different continent at least twice a month. If you are lucky he will "
"fly close to Alice soon. So you will go and meet with Trent to sign keys. "
"Then you will drop Alice a note that Trent will be at her place soon and ask "
"her if she can meet with him too to sign keys. After all this has happened "
"you know that Trent's key can be trusted and Trent knows that Alice's key "
"can be trusted. If you trust Trent that he has carefully checked Alice's "
"identity then you can also trust her key."
msgstr ""
"Toda zakaj je pomembno, kako skrbno ste preverili Anino identiteto? Komu bi "
"moralo biti mar? Obstaja drugačen način za rešitev vaše težave z identiteto "
"Ane. Če ne morete kmalu obiskati Ane, samo pomislite na Tomaža. Veste, da "
"ima tudi Tomaž par ključev. In Tomaž je svetovni popotnik, saj je vsaj "
"dvakrat na mesec na drugi celini. Če boste imeli srečo, bo kmalu prišel "
"blizu Ane. Torej se boste srečali s Tomažem, da podpišete ključe. Nato boste "
"Ani poslali sporočilo, da bo Tomaž kmalu pri njej, in jo vprašali, ali se "
"lahko sreča tudi z njim, da podpišeta ključe. Ko se je vse to zgodilo, "
"veste, da lahko zaupate Tomaževemu ključu in Tomaž ve, da lahko zaupate "
"Aninemu ključu. Če zaupate Tomažu, da je skrbno preveril Anino identiteto, "
"potem lahko zaupate tudi njenemu ključu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These relationships between keys and their owners form a so called web of "
"trust. Within that web there are some important values that define how "
"trustworthy a particular key is. The first thing is how carefully the "
"identity of the key owner was checked. That is the value you have seen above "
"in the secret key selection window. For example you will likely know how to "
"verify your local countries identity card but one from a completely "
"different country may be hard to verify. So you could say that you have very "
"carefully checked Trent's identity because you have seen his identity card "
"and it looks very much the same as yours. But Trent, although he has seen "
"both Alice's identity card and driver license might say he has only done "
"casual checking of her identity as he is not absolutely sure about the "
"documents from that part of the world."
msgstr ""
"Ti odnosi med ključi in njihovimi lastniki tvorijo tako imenovano mrežo "
"zaupanja. V tej mreži je nekaj pomembnih vrednosti, ki določajo, kako "
"zaupanja vreden je določen ključ. Prva stvar je, kako natančno je bila "
"preverjena identiteta lastnika ključa. To je vrednost, ki ste jo videli "
"zgoraj v oknu za izbiro skrivnega ključa. Verjetno boste na primer vedeli, "
"kako preveriti osebno izkaznico iz svoje lokalne države, vendar bo osebno "
"izkaznico iz popolnoma druge države morda težko preveriti. Torej bi lahko "
"rekli, da ste zelo skrbno preverili Tomaževo identiteto, ker ste videli "
"njegovo osebno izkaznico in je videti zelo podobna vaši. Toda Tomaž, čeprav "
"je videl Anino osebno izkaznico in vozniško dovoljenje, bi lahko rekel, da "
"je le navadno preveril njeno identiteto, saj ni povsem prepričan o "
"dokumentih iz tistega dela sveta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The next important value is how much you trust the other person to verify "
"documents. You know Trent is good at that. But George for example is no one "
"you would call smart. He barely looked at your id card when you met him for "
"key signing. You are sure that George is the person he pretends to be as you "
"checked his documents carefully. But he doesn't seem to really care if he "
"checks other people so you will have a high trust in the key of George but a "
"very low trust in the signatures of George. If you open the <link linkend="
"\"keyproperties\">properties</link> of a key you will find the field "
"<guilabel>Owner Trust</guilabel>. This is how much you trust the key owner "
"when he signs keys. This value will not be exported, it is completely up to "
"your personal preference."
msgstr ""
"Naslednja pomembna vrednost je, koliko zaupate drugi osebi pri preverjanju "
"dokumentov. Veste, da je Tomaž dober v tem. Toda Gregor na primer ni nekdo, "
"ki bi ga označili za pametnega. Komaj je pogledal vašo osebno izkaznico, ko "
"ste se srečali z njim za podpisovanje ključev. Prepričani ste, da je Gregor "
"oseba, za katero se predstavlja, saj ste natančno pregledali njegove "
"dokumente. Vendar se zdi, da ni tako pazljiv, ko sam preverja druge ljudi, "
"tako da boste zelo zaupali ključu Gregorja, vendar zelo malo zaupali "
"podpisom Gregorja. Če odprete <link linkend=\"keyproperties\">lastnosti</"
"link> ključa, boste našli polje <guilabel>Zaupanje lastniku</guilabel>. To "
"je, koliko zaupate lastniku ključa, ko podpiše ključe. Ta vrednost ne bo "
"izvožena, popolnoma je odvisna od vaših osebnih preferenc."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you should have an idea how the web of trust is built, what the owner "
"and key trust values are for, and why you always should be very careful when "
"checking identities: other people might rely on you. But one element in the "
"process is still unverified: the email addresses in the keys you signed. "
"Creating a new user identity in your key with the email address of Alice or "
"Trent will only take a few mouse clicks. You have verified that Trent really "
"owns his key. But noone has checked until now that Trent really controls the "
"email addresses of his user identities."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj bi morali razumeti, kako je zgrajena mreža zaupanja, čemu so namenjene "
"vrednosti zaupanja lastniku in ključem, ter zakaj morate biti vedno zelo "
"previdni pri preverjanju identitete: drugi ljudje se morda zanašajo na vas. "
"Toda en element v procesu še vedno ni preverjen: e-poštni naslovi v ključih, "
"ki ste jih podpisali. Ustvarjanje nove uporabniške identitete v vašem ključu "
"z e-poštnim naslovom Ane ali Tomaža bo trajalo le nekaj klikov. Preverili "
"ste, da je Tomaž res lastnik svojega ključa. Toda nihče do sedaj ni "
"preveril, ali Tomaž res nadzoruje elektronske naslove na svojih uporabniških "
"identitetah."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:400
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you choose <guimenuitem>Sign and Mail User ID...</guimenuitem> from the "
"menu instead you can close that gap. The idea is that you will sign the key "
"as usual and afterwards it will be split into pieces. Every piece will only "
"contain one user identity of Trent's key and your signature to it. This will "
"be encrypted with Trent's key and sent only to the email address given in "
"that identity. Only if Trent can receive this mail and decrypt the message "
"he will be able to import that signature into his key ring. You will not "
"upload your signatures, this is entirely up to him. If your signature will "
"show up on a key server you can be sure that Trent really controls both his "
"key as well as the email address you signed. The signatures you make in this "
"process will also be not part of your keyring. So right after you signed "
"Trent's key it will still be shown as untrusted in your keyring. Once Trent "
"has received your mail and imported your signature into his keyring he can "
"upload them to a keyserver. When you refresh his key from a keyserver you "
"will get the new signatures. While that may sound inconvenient first it "
"makes sure that you will not by accident see one of his identities as "
"trusted that he does not control. Only the signatures that show up on a "
"keyserver are those where everyone, including you, can be sure that he "
"really controls the corresponding email addresses."
msgstr ""
"Če namesto tega v meniju izberete <guimenuitem>Podpiši in pošlji ID "
"uporabnika ...</guimenuitem>, lahko zapolniš to vrzel. Ideja je, da boste "
"ključ podpisali kot običajno, nato pa bo razdeljen na dele. Vsak kos bo "
"vseboval samo eno uporabniško identiteto Tomaževega ključa in vaš podpis. To "
"bo šifrirano s Tomaževim ključem in poslano samo na e-poštni naslov, naveden "
"v tej identiteti. Samo če lahko Tomaž prejme to pošto in dešifrira "
"sporočilo, bo lahko uvozil ta podpis v svojo shrambo s ključi. Vi ne boste "
"naložili svojih podpisov, to je v celoti odvisno od njega. Če se bo vaš "
"podpis pojavil na strežniku s ključi, ste lahko prepričani, da Tomaž "
"resnično nadzoruje tako svoj ključ kot tudi e-poštni naslov, ki ste ga "
"podpisali. Podpisi, ki jih naredite v tem procesu, tudi ne bodo del vaše "
"shrambe s ključi. Takoj po tem, ko podpišete Tomažev ključ, bo v vaši "
"shrambi s ključi še vedno prikazan kot nevreden zaupanja. Ko Tomaž prejme "
"vašo pošto in uvozi vaš podpis v svojo shrambo s ključi, jih lahko naloži na "
"strežnik s ključi. Ko osvežite njegov ključ s strežnika s ključi, boste "
"dobili nove podpise. Čeprav se to najprej morda sliši neprijetno, "
"zagotavlja, da ne boste slučajno imeli eno od njegovih identitet, ki je "
"morda sploh ne nadzoruje, za zaupanja vredno. Samo podpisi, ki se prikažejo "
"na strežniku s ključi, so tisti, pri katerih so lahko vsi, vključno z vami, "
"prepričani, da on resnično nadzoruje navedene e-poštne naslove."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working with key servers"
msgstr "Delo z strežniki s ključi"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:410
#, no-c-format
msgid "Communication with key servers"
msgstr "Komunikacija s strežniki s ključi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:412
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The public part of a key pair is usually stored on a key server. These "
"servers allow anyone to search for a key belonging to a specific person or "
"mail address. The signatures are also stored on these servers."
msgstr ""
"Javni del para ključev je ponavadi shranjen na strežniku s ključi. Ti "
"strežniki dopuščajo komur koli, da poišče ključ, ki pripada določeni osebi "
"ali e-poštnem naslovu. Na teh strežnikih so shranjeni tudi podpisi."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:415
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here's a screen shot of keyserver window."
msgstr "Tukaj je posnetek zaslona okna strežnika s ključi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This dialog gives you access to the keyservers. You can search and import "
"keys from a keyserver as well as export keys to a server. An example of "
"searching and importing is when you want to write a mail to someone new. If "
"you would like to encrypt your mail to your contact you can search if he or "
"she has a public key on the key servers. If you have created a new key pair "
"or have signed someone else's key you might want to export the public key "
"(possibly with new signatures) to a keyserver."
msgstr ""
"To pogovorno okno vam omogoča dostop do strežnikov s ključi. Tu lahko iščete "
"in uvažate ključe iz strežnikov, kot tudi nalagate ključe na strežnik. "
"Ključe se išče in uvaža, ko npr. želite poslati e-sporočilo nekomu novemu. "
"Če želite zašifrirati sporočilo, ki ga pošiljate svojemu kontaktu, lahko na "
"strežniku poiščete, če ima na njem ta oseba svoj javni ključ. Če ste "
"ustvarili nov par ali ste podpisali ključ nekoga drugega, je pametno, da "
"javni ključ izvozite (po možnosti z novimi podpisi) na strežnik s ključi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:423
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most keyservers synchronize their data between each others so you will get "
"similar search results regardless which server you use. Since there are "
"exceptions of this rule you can choose the keyserver to use in this dialog. "
"It's usually a good idea to choose a default keyserver that is located close "
"to you (i.e. in your country or on your continent) as they usually respond "
"faster to your queries."
msgstr ""
"Večina strežnikov s ključi sinhronizira svoje podatke med sabo, zato boste "
"dobili podobne rezultate ne glede na to, kateri strežnik uporabljate. Ker pa "
"obstajajo izjeme, lahko sami izberete strežnik, ki ga boste uporabljali v "
"tem pogovoru. Ponavadi je pametno izbrati privzeti strežnik, ki se nahaja "
"blizu vam (i.e. v vaši državi ali celini), ker se običajno odzivajo hitreje "
"vašim zahtevam."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:424
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please note that everything you upload to a keyserver usually stays there "
"forever. This is one reason you should usually limit the lifetime of your "
"keys. Also note that the keyservers are sometimes scanned by spammers for "
"email addresses."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da vse kar naložite na strežnik s ključi, ponavadi tam ostane "
"za vedno. To je eden od razlogov, zakaj je dobro omejiti uporabnost vaših "
"ključev. Upoštevajte tudi, da te strežnike velikokrat skenirajo pošiljatelji "
"nezaželene pošte za e-naslove."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:428
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key server search results"
msgstr "Rezultati iskanja na strežniku s ključi"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:430
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is an example of the results of a keyserver search."
msgstr "To je primer rezultatov iskanja po strežniku ključev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:437
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All results of a search are displayed in this window. This picture shows a "
"search for &quot;@kde.org&quot; addresses which showed up 244 results. Using "
"the search field the displayed list was reduced to a single key. This key "
"has two matches: the primary user id itself matches the search string as "
"well as one of the other user ids."
msgstr ""
"Vsi rezultati vašega iskanja so prikazani v tem oknu. Ta slika prikazuje "
"iskanje naslovov &quot;@kde.org&quot;, ki je pokazalo 244 ujemanj. Z uporabo "
"polja za iskanje se je prikazani seznam zmanjšal na en sam ključ. Ta ključ "
"ima dve ujemanji: ID prvotnega uporabnika se ujema z iskalnim nizom kot tudi "
"eden izmed drugih ID-jev uporabnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can select one or more keys to import. The ids of those keys are shown "
"in the <guilabel>Keys to import</guilabel> field at the bottom of the "
"window. When you click on <guibutton>Import</guibutton> the key server is "
"contacted again and the keys are fetched into your keyring."
msgstr ""
"Izberete lahko enega ali več ključev za uvoz. ID-ji teh ključev so prikazani "
"v polju <guilabel>Ključi za uvoz</guilabel> na dnu okna. Ko kliknete na gumb "
"<guibutton>Uvozi</guibutton>, se ponovno kontaktira strežnik in ključi so "
"pridobljeni v vašo shrambo s ključi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring &kgpg;"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje &kgpg;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:448
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configuration is accessible through the &kgpg; applet menu (&RMB; click on "
"the applet) or through the main menu ( <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure KGpg</guimenuitem></menuchoice>). You can set "
"default parameters for encryption, decryption, user interface and applet. "
"Most encryption options are directly related to gpg and are documented in "
"it's <ulink url=\"man:gpg\">man page</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Konfiguracija je dostopna preko &kgpg;-jevega aplet menija (desni klik na "
"aplet) ali preko glavnega menija (<menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj KGpg</guimenuitem></menuchoice>). "
"Nastavite lahko privzete parametre za šifriranje, dešifriranje, uporabniški "
"vmesnik in aplet. Večina šifrirnih možnosti so neposredno povezane z gpg-jem "
"in so dokumentirane v <ulink url=\"man:gpg\">straneh priročnika</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encryption"
msgstr "Šifriranje"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "A screen shot of the option dialog with encryption tab opened"
msgstr ""
"Posnetek zaslona pogovornega okna z možnostmi z odprtim zavihkom Šifriranje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:463
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can configure special options to be passed to GnuPG to change the "
"encryption behavior. For detailed description please have a look at the "
"GnuPG manual."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko konfigurirate posebne možnosti, s katerimi spremenite delovanje "
"GnuPG. Za podroben opis si poglejte priročnik za GnuPG."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:465
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>ASCII armored encryption</guilabel>: this causes encrypted files "
"to be stored in a format that uses only printable ASCII characters and has "
"short lines. Files stored this way are bigger than the files in binary "
"format but are easier to send &eg; by email."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Šifriranje na podlagi ASCII</guilabel>: ta možnost povzroči, da so "
"šifrirane datoteke shranjene v formatu, ki uporablja le natisljive znake in "
"ima kratke vrstice. Take datoteke so večje kot tiste v binarnem formatu, "
"vendar jih je lažje pošiljati &eg; po e-pošti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:466
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Allow encryption with untrusted keys</guilabel>: this allows you "
"to encrypt files with keys that are not trusted by you."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Dovoli šifriranje s ključi, ki niso zaupanja vredni</guilabel>: to "
"vam omogoča, da šifrirate datoteke tudi s ključi, ki jim vi ne zaupate."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:467
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>PGP 6 compatibility</guilabel>: encrypted files are compatible "
"with the older PGP6 standard. This disables certain features so you should "
"only use this if really needed."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Združljivost s PGP 6</guilabel>: šifrirane datoteke bodo "
"združljive z starejšimi PGP6 standardi. Ta možnost bo onemogočila nekatere "
"funkcije, zato jo uporabljajte le, če jo res potrebujete."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Hide user id</guilabel>: this removes all evidence of the receiver "
"from the encrypted file. In case the transmission is intercepted noone could "
"gain information about the recipient from the file. If the receiver has "
"multiple keys he needs to try which one was used."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Skrij uporabniški ID</guilabel>: to odstrani vse dokaze o "
"prejemniku iz šifrirane datoteke. V primeru, da bi bil prenos prestrežen, ne "
"more nihče pridobiti informacij o prejemniku iz datoteke. Če ima prejemnik "
"več ključev, bo moral poskusiti, kateri je bil uporabljen."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:469
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Always encrypt with</guilabel>: all encryptions are additionally "
"encrypted with this key. If you set this to one of your private keys this "
"makes sure you can read all data you encrypted by the price of bigger "
"messages."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Vedno šifriraj z</guilabel>: vsa že zašifrirana sporočila bodo še "
"dodatno šifrirane s tem ključem. Če za ta ključ določite enega vaših "
"zasebnih ključev, vam to zagotovi, da boste lahko prebrali vse podatke, ki "
"ste jih šifrirali, vendar za ceno večjih sporočil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:470
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Encrypt files with</guilabel>: behaves like <guilabel>Always "
"encrypt with</guilabel> for file encryption."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Šifriraj datoteke z</guilabel>: obnaša se kot <guilabel>Vedno "
"šifriraj z</guilabel>, le da za šifriranje datotek."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Custom encryption command</guilabel>: if you need to pass some "
"unusual options to GnuPG you can specify the command line here. Most users "
"will not need this."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Ukaz šifriranja po meri</guilabel>: če morate vnesti nekaj "
"nenavadnih možnosti v GnuPG, lahko tukaj določite ukazno vrstico. Večina "
"uporabnikov tega ne potrebuje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Use *.pgp extension for encrypted files</guilabel>: if you check "
"this option encrypted files will be named as the input file with the "
"extension <literal role=\"extension\">.pgp</literal> added, otherwise the "
"extension <literal role=\"extension\">.gpg</literal> is used."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Uporabi pripono *.pgp za šifriranje datotek</guilabel>: Če "
"obkljukate to možnost, bodo zašifrirane datoteke poimenovane kot vhodne z "
"dodano pripono <literal role=\"extension\">.pgp</literal>. V nasprotnem "
"primeru bo uporabljena pripona <literal role=\"extension\">.gpg</literal>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:477
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decryption"
msgstr "Dešifriranje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can specify a custom decryption command. This option is seldomly "
"needed and only useful for advanced users that know of GnuPGs command line "
"options."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko določite poljuben ukaz za dešifriranje. Ta možnost je redko "
"rabljena in uporabna le za napredne uporabnike, ki poznajo GnuPG-jeve "
"možnosti ukazne vrstice."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:483
#, no-c-format
msgid "Appearance"
msgstr "Izgled"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:484
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can configure the way &kgpg; looks to you. Possible settings are "
"the colors that reflect the different levels of key trust in the <link "
"linkend=\"keymanager\">key manager</link> and the font settings for the "
"<link linkend=\"editor\">editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko prilagodite izgled &kgpg;-ja. Možne nastavitve so barve, ki "
"odražajo stopnjo zaupanja v ključ v <link linkend=\"keymanager"
"\">upravljalniku ključev</link> in nastavitve vrste pisave za <link linkend="
"\"editor\">urejevalnik</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:488
#, no-c-format
msgid "GnuPG Settings"
msgstr "GnuPG Nastavitve"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can configure which gpg binary and which <guilabel>configuration "
"file</guilabel> and home folder are used. These values are autodetected on "
"first start and should already work."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko prilagodite, katere binarne datoteke in katere "
"<guilabel>konfiguracijske datoteke</guilabel> bodo uporabljene in katera "
"mapa bo uporabljena za domačo. Te vrednosti so samodejno zaznane ob prvem "
"zagonu in bi morale že delovati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the <ulink url=\"man:gpg-agent\">GnuPG agent</ulink> makes work with "
"GnuPG more comfortable as you do not need to type in your password for every "
"action. It is cached in memory for a while so any operation that would "
"require a password can immediately be done. Note that this may allow other "
"people to use your private keys if you leave your session accessible to them."
msgstr ""
"Delo z GnuPG bo bolj udobno, če boste uporabljali <ulink url=\"man:gpg-agent"
"\">GnuPG agent</ulink>, saj vam ne bo treba za vsako dejavnost vnašati "
"gesla. Geslo bo začasno shranjeno v spominu, zato bo vsako dejanje, za "
"katerega potrebujete geslo, v hipu narejeno. Upoštevajte, da lahko to "
"omogoči drugim, da uporabljajo vaše zasebne ključe, če jim pustite dostop do "
"vaše seje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:494
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key Servers"
msgstr "Strežniki s Ključi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:495
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can create a list of keyservers that are shown to you when you open "
"the <link linkend=\"keyserver\">key server dialog</link>. If you run GnuPG "
"from the command line only the key server you set as default here will be "
"used."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko ustvarite seznam strežnikov s ključi, ki bodo prikazani, ko "
"boste odprli <link linkend=\"keyserver\">pogovorno okno za strežnike s "
"ključi</link>. Če boste zagnali GnuPG iz ukazne vrstice, bo uporabljen le "
"privzet strežnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The protocol used for communication with the key servers is based on &HTTP;, "
"so it makes sense in some environments to <guilabel>honor the &HTTP; proxy "
"when available</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Protokol uporabljen za komunikacijo s strežniki s ključi je zasnovan na "
"&HTTP;, zato je v nekaterih okoliščinah smiselno <guilabel>upoštevati &HTTP; "
"proxy strežnik, ko je ta na voljo</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:500
#, no-c-format
msgid "Misc"
msgstr "Razno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:501
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section allows the setting of some different features that do not fit "
"into the other sections. You can configure for example to <guilabel>start "
"KGpg automatically at login</guilabel>. The option <guilabel>use mouse "
"selection instead of clipboard</guilabel> changes if selection happens by "
"mouse and pasting by middle mouse button or if all operations are done by "
"keyboard shortcuts."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek omogoča nastavitev nekaj  različnih funkcij, ki ne spadajo pod "
"druge razdelke. Tu lahko na primer nastavite, da se bo <guilabel>KGpg zagnal "
"samodejno ob vpisu</guilabel>. Možnost <guilabel>uporabi miškino izbiro "
"namesto odložišča</guilabel> se spremeni, če izbiranje poteka z miško in "
"prilepljenje s srednjim gumbom miške ali če se vse operacije izvajajo z "
"bližnjicami na tipkovnici."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also change if the systray icon of &kgpg; is shown or not and what "
"action happens if the icon is clicked with the &LMB;. If the systray icon is "
"shown closing the &kgpg; window will minimize the application to tray. If "
"the systray icon is not shown &kgpg; will exit when all windows are closed."
msgstr ""
"Prav tako lahko spremenite, ali bo &kgpg; ikona prikazana v sistemski "
"vrstici ali ne in katero dejanje se izvede, če je ikona kliknjena z levim "
"klikom. Če je prikaz ikone sistemske vrstice omogočen, bo izhod iz okna "
"&kgpg;-ja minimiziral aplikacijo v sistemsko vrstico. Če je prikaz "
"onemogočen, se bo &kgpg; ustavil, ko bodo zaprta vsa okna."

